## ⚙️ PHASE 4 — COMPILE & RUN (with Retry Logic)

### Retry Protocol — Maximum 5 Attempts Per File/Module

For EACH attempt (attempt #1 through #5):

Step 4.1 — Compile
- Maven:  mvn test-compile -q
- Gradle: ./gradlew compileTestJava

Step 4.2 — Analyze Compile Errors (if any)
- cannot find symbol        → Add missing import or fix class name
- incompatible types        → Fix type mismatch in test assertion or stub
- method not found          → Fix method signature — re-read source file
- package does not exist    → Add dependency to pom.xml/build.gradle
- ambiguous method call     → Add explicit cast to argument

Step 4.3 — Run Tests
- Maven:  mvn test -q
- Gradle: ./gradlew test

Step 4.4 — Analyze Test Failures (if any)
- NullPointerException              → Add missing when(...).thenReturn(...) stub
- WantedButNotInvoked               → Fix verify() call — check method name/args
- UnnecessaryStubbingException      → Remove unused when(...) stubs
- AssertionFailedError              → Re-read source logic and fix expected value
- MissingMethodInvocationException  → Fix Mockito chaining syntax
- StrictStubs violation             → Switch to lenient stubbing or remove unused stubs

Step 4.5 — Generate Coverage Report
- Maven:  mvn jacoco:report -q
- Gradle: ./gradlew jacocoTestReport

Step 4.6 — Read Coverage Report
- Maven:  target/site/jacoco/index.html
- Gradle: build/reports/jacoco/test/html/index.html
- Extract line coverage percentage per class
- List all classes below 90% with their current coverage %

Step 4.7 — If Coverage < 90%
- Identify exactly which lines/branches are uncovered from the report
- Generate additional test cases targeting those specific lines
- Go back to Step 4.1 (next attempt)

Step 4.8 — If Attempt 5 Fails
Output this report:

  COVERAGE REPORT AFTER 5 ATTEMPTS
  ----------------------------------
  Classes at 90%+: [list]
  Classes below 90%: [class name] → [X%]
    Uncovered lines: [line numbers]
    Reason: [e.g., private method, dead code, static initializer]
    Recommendation: [e.g., extract method, make testable, manual test needed]

